[SN]TITLE[SN]
Cranfield University fined after worker injured in bomb explosion

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A university has been fined after a worker suffered serious injuries when a cluster bomblet he was trying to deactivate exploded.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Swindon Crown Court heard no risk assessment for the activity had been carried out at Cranfield University.
The institution pleaded guilty and was fined £80,000 with £75,000 costs.
The employee suffered severe chest and abdominal injuries and had surgery to remove metal from his colon after the explosion on 4 February 2011.
He also suffered cuts on his face and shoulder, and nerve damage to his right hand.
